            <a href="/Auth/Login"><i class="bi bi-stars"></i>Try DwellScript Free</a>
        </div>

        <h2>The bottom line</h2>
        <p>
            A long vacancy is rarely a market problem. It's almost always a listing problem — a weak headline, poor photos, unanswered objections, or pricing that's slightly off. Work through each of these systematically and your vacancy period will shorten.
        </p>
        <p>
            Start with photos and headline. Those two changes alone account for the majority of listing performance improvement.
        </p>

